<para id="fs-idp89607040">(a) torr</para>
<para id="fs-idm95742832">(b) Pa</para>
<para id="fs-idm80328752">(c) bar</para>
<media id="fs-idm92729728" alt="A diagram of a closed-end manometer is shown. To the upper left is a spherical container labeled, “gas.” This container is connected by a valve to a U-shaped tube which is labeled “closed end” at the upper right end. The container and a portion of tube that follows are shaded pink. The lower portion of the U-shaped tube is shaded grey with the height of the gray region being greater on the right side than on the left. The difference in height of 26.4 c m is indicated with horizontal line segments and arrows." class="scaled-down">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="CNX_Chem_09_01_Manometer5_img.jpg"/>
</media>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm48939344">
<para id="fs-idm83006352">(a) 264 torr; (b) 35,200 Pa; (c) 0.352 bar</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
